The British High Commission hosted a cocktail party at the English Point Marina for governors, hoteliers and businessmen to mark the opening of the coast chapter of the British Chamber of Commerce Kenya. The event held on Tuesday, brought together UK envoy Nic Hailey, Governors Hassan Joho (Mombasa), John Mruttu (Taita Taveta) and Issa Timmamy (Lamu) and Mvita MP Abdulswamad Nassir (Mvita). The BCCK promotes trade links between Kenya and Great Britain. Now in its fourth year of operations, the chamber represents over 200 members, from FTSE 100 companies down to individual consultants. Its membership includes some of the largest tax payers in Kenya.